cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software or its accompanying paper, please cite it as below."
title: "ATM: Adapter-Guided Atomization with CID Broker for Single-Domain Multi-Vendor LLM Code Co-Synthesis"
abstract: >
  ATM is a single-workspace pre-write admission framework for multi-agent
  LLM code co-synthesis. It provides a two-tier Contract Identifier (CID),
  a seven-layer hard gate, Adaptive Granularity Refinement (AGR), a
  format-agnostic adapter subsystem with content-addressed CAS, a neutral
  steward arbitration flow, the Team Agents Wave Mode for batch admission,
  and the Git Boundary Admission Bridge that reuses the in-process
  admission pipeline at git push time.
